<div class="brand">📚 ENGLISH CODING · 영어코딩</div>
<h1>⚙️ M002 Week 7 — Pistons</h1>
<p><strong>Topic:</strong> Pistons and Mazes · <strong>Course:</strong> Maze Madness · <strong>Level:</strong> Intermediate · <strong>Time:</strong> about 35 minutes</p>
<p>A piston opens a path when a lever powers it. Flip the lever, then cross the gap while the path is open.</p>
<hr />
<h2>1 · Predict 🔮</h2>
<p>Write what happens.</p>
<pre><code>move forward
interact ahead
move forward
</code></pre>
<p><strong>The agent reaches a lever and flips it. A piston opens the path. Can the agent cross now?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<pre><code>if gap ahead:
    interact ahead
otherwise:
    move forward
</code></pre>
<p><strong>The agent is on solid ground, no gap. What does it do?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<hr />
<h2>2 · Trace 👣</h2>
<pre><code>keep doing forever:
    if gap ahead:
        interact ahead
        move forward
    otherwise:
        move forward
</code></pre>
<p><strong>Say in plain English what the agent does at a gap, and what it does on solid ground.</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<hr />
<h2>3 · Fill the Code Blank 🧩</h2>
<p>The agent flips the lever only when it sees a gap ahead.</p>
<pre><code class="language-python">if not agent.detect(BLOCK, FORWARD):
    agent.____(...)
    agent.move(FORWARD, 1)
else:
    agent.move(FORWARD, 1)
</code></pre>
<p><strong>Word bank:</strong> <code>interact</code> · <code>turn</code> · <code>detect</code></p>
<p><strong>Write the missing word:</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<hr />
<h2>4 · Spot One Bug 🐛</h2>
<p>The agent should power the piston <strong>first</strong>, then cross the gap it opens. This code crosses first.</p>
<pre><code class="language-python">agent.move(FORWARD, 1)
agent.move(FORWARD, 1)
agent.interact(...)
</code></pre>
<p><strong>Write the fixed code (flip the lever before the gap):</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>One sentence: why was it wrong?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<hr />
<h2>5 · Show Your Work 📸🎥</h2>
<p>Open your homework world. The maze has a gap and a piston that opens it. Walk the agent to the lever, flip it, cross while the path is open, and reach the goal.</p>
<p>Record <strong>one video</strong> (a phone is fine). Show two things:</p>
<p><strong>1 · Your code.</strong> Scroll through it. Say what each part does.</p>
<p><strong>2 · Your build.</strong> Point the camera. Name the parts.</p>
<p>Fill the blanks:</p>
<blockquote>
<p>Today I built ______.</p>
<p>I built it using this code: ______.</p>
<p>In this code I used ______.</p>
<p>The hardest part was ______.</p>
<p>That part was hard because ______.</p>
</blockquote>
<p><strong>Write your lines here, then say them in your video.</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

